# livediagram MCP server (spec/62). No secrets live here: the MCP forwards the
# caller's Bearer lvd_ token to the api worker over a service binding, and the
# OAuth consent + token mint authenticate via Clerk in apps/live + apps/api.
#
# Configure via wrangler, not env vars:
#   - the API service binding (apps/api) — see wrangler.toml
#   - the OAUTH_KV namespace: `wrangler kv namespace create OAUTH_KV`, then put
#     the id in wrangler.toml
#
# The MCP is gated on auth being enabled end-to-end: with Clerk unset, the
# api's /api/oauth/exchange rejects every caller and the consent page has no
# signed-in user, so no token can be minted (spec/62 §3.7). A no-auth
# self-host simply doesn't deploy this worker.
